      "content": "Here's a list of basic rules for professional etiquette and acting sophisticated in a global business setting:\n\n1. Dress code: Stick to classic, timeless pieces, and avoid anything too flashy or revealing, especially for power meetings or high-end events. Tailored suits, crisp white shirts, and quality leather shoes are a must for men, while women should opt for elegant dresses or tailored pantsuits.\n2. Grooming: Ensure your hair is well-groomed, and your nails are trimmed and clean. Avoid excessive perfume or cologne, and opt for subtle, sophisticated fragrances.\n3. Body language: Maintain good posture, make eye contact, and use open, confident body language. Avoid crossing your arms or legs, which can give the impression of being defensive or closed off.\n4. Table manners: Use your napkin, keep your elbows off the table, and don't talk with your mouth full. Women should avoid crossing their legs, which can be seen as provocative.\n5. Communication: Be clear, concise, and respectful in your communication. Avoid using slang or overly technical jargon, and try to understand and appreciate different cultures and customs.\n6. Respect for cultural differences: Be aware of cultural norms and customs, especially when interacting",
